<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
China (Chongqing*, Fujian, Shanxi), Japan, South &amp; North Korea, Taiwan. Introduced to Europe and North America (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4039/Ent12293-1" author="Atkinson, TH" journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="92 - 104" refId="B5" refString="Atkinson, TH, Rabaglia, RJ, Bright, DE, 1990. Newly detected exotic species of Xyleborus (Coleoptera: Scolytidae) with a revised key to species in eastern North America. The Canadian Entomologist 122: 92 - 104, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4039/Ent12293-1" title="Newly detected exotic species of Xyleborus (Coleoptera: Scolytidae) with a revised key to species in eastern North America." url="https://doi.org/10.4039/Ent12293-1" volume="122" year="1990">Atkinson et al. 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1772.1.2" author="Faccoli, M" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="55 - 62" refId="B158" refString="Faccoli, M, 2008. First record of Xyleborus atratus Eichhoff from Europe with an illustrated key to the European Xyleborini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Zootaxa 1772: 55 - 62, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1772.1.2" title="First record of Xyleborus atratus Eichhoff from Europe with an illustrated key to the European Xyleborini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1772.1.2" volume="1772" year="2008">Faccoli 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.768.24697" author="Gomez, DF" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="19 - 68" refId="B175" refString="Gomez, DF, Rabaglia, RJ, Fairbanks, KEO, Hulcr, J, 2018a. North American Xyleborini north of Mexico: a review and key to genera and species (Coleoptera, Curculionidae, Scolytinae). ZooKeys 768: 19 - 68, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.768.24697" title="North American Xyleborini north of Mexico: a review and key to genera and species (Coleoptera, Curculionidae, Scolytinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.768.24697" volume="768" year="2018 a">Gomez et al. 2018a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="host">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Host plants.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Polyphagous (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1772.1.2" author="Faccoli, M" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="55 - 62" refId="B158" refString="Faccoli, M, 2008. First record of Xyleborus atratus Eichhoff from Europe with an illustrated key to the European Xyleborini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Zootaxa 1772: 55 - 62, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1772.1.2" title="First record of Xyleborus atratus Eichhoff from Europe with an illustrated key to the European Xyleborini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1772.1.2" volume="1772" year="2008">Faccoli 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2602.1.1" author="Beaver, RA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 47" refId="B22" refString="Beaver, RA, Liu, L-Y, 2010. An annotated synopsis of Taiwanese bark and ambrosia beetles, with new synonymy, new combinations and new records (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Zootaxa 2602: 1 - 47, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2602.1.1" title="An annotated synopsis of Taiwanese bark and ambrosia beetles, with new synonymy, new combinations and new records (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2602.1.1" volume="2602" year="2010">Beaver and Liu 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.funeco.2016.07.002" author="Kasson, MT" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Ecology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="86 - 96" refId="B225" refString="Kasson, MT, Wickert, KL, Stauder, CM, Macias, AM, Berger, MC, Simmons, DR, Short, DPG, DeVallance, DB, Hulcr, J, 2016. Mutualism with aggressive wood-degrading Flavodon ambrosius (Polyporales) facilitates niche expansion and communal social structure in Ambrosiophilus ambrosia beetles. Fungal Ecology 23: 86 - 96, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.funeco.2016.07.002" title="Mutualism with aggressive wood-degrading Flavodon ambrosius (Polyporales) facilitates niche expansion and communal social structure in Ambrosiophilus ambrosia beetles." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.funeco.2016.07.002" volume="23" year="2016">Kasson et al. (2016)</bibRefCitation>
have shown that the symbiotic association of the species with the fungus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="D. R. Simmons, You Li, C. C. Bateman &amp; Hulcr" authorityYear="2016" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Meruliaceae" genus="Flavodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Flavodon ambrosius" order="Polyporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ambrosius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Flavodon ambrosius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has allowed niche expansion with large, long-lived, interconnecting colonies, overlapping generations, and pre-dispersal oviposition by young females.
</paragraph>
